  "notes": [
    "This case report describes a complex diagnostic challenge involving cyclic ACTH-dependent Cushing syndrome with unusual response patterns to desmopressin testing.",
    "The patient showed no peripheral ACTH response to desmopressin but had a marked central response during IPSS, which is an unusual finding.",
    "The case highlights the importance of using desmopressin during IPSS even when peripheral testing shows no response."
